From 93e1f599b50ea7079a691519a81e45062e64fc40 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bartosz Golaszewski <bartosz.golaszewski@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 14:50:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 12/22] tools: gpioinfo: use correct function to free the
 resolver

struct line_resolver should be freed with free_line_resolver() while
gpioinfo uses a regular free() resulting in a leak of multiple objects.
This issue is not really harmful as gpioinfo exits right after that but
fix it for consistency.

Fixes: 8ffb6489286f ("tools: line name focussed rework")
Reported-by: 4fqr <4fqr@proton.me>
Tested-by: Vincent Fazio <vfazio@xes-inc.com>
Reviewed-by: Vincent Fazio <vfazio@xes-inc.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260407-treewide-fixes-v1-13-66c9744a56a3@oss.qualcomm.com
Signed-off-by: Bartosz Golaszewski <bartosz.golaszewski@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 tools/gpioinfo.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tools/gpioinfo.c b/tools/gpioinfo.c
index 4619ca7..007d944 100644
--- a/tools/gpioinfo.c
+++ b/tools/gpioinfo.c
@@ -266,7 +266,7 @@ int main(int argc, char **argv)
 	validate_resolution(resolver, cfg.chip_id);
 	if (argc && resolver->num_found != argc)
 		ret = EXIT_FAILURE;
-	free(resolver);
+	free_line_resolver(resolver);
 
 	return ret;
 }
-- 
2.53.0

